results.name: Self-inverse permutation of nonnegative integers: a(n) = A264985(A263273(A264985(n))).
comment: A263273 conjugated with the permutation obtained from its odd bisection.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..6561
Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
formula: As a composition of related permutations:
mathematica: f[n_] := Block[{g, h}, g[x_] := x/3^IntegerExponent[x, 3]; h[x_] := x/g@ x; If[n == 0, 0, FromDigits[Reverse@ IntegerDigits[#, 3], 3] &@ g[n] h[n]]]; s = Select[f /@ Range@ 5000, OddQ]; t = Table[(s[[n + 1]] - 1)/2, {n, 0, 1000}]; Table[t[[f[t[[n + 1]]] + 1]], {n, 0, 83}] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Jan 04 2016, after _Jean-François Alcover_ at A263273 *)
xref: Cf. A265369, A265904, A266401, A266403 (other conjugates or similar derivations of A263273).
